  "text": "tissues. In the cell analysis, the spectra at 950-1000, 1050-1100, 1120-1130, 1120-1200, 1200-1300, and 1300-1350 cm −1 and the peaks around 1100, 1030, and 1450 cm −1 were higher in glioma cells than in normal astrocytes. Those peaks are derived from the chemical structure of DNA, proteins and lipids as described in Table 1 . Several biologically significant peaks exist in those regions as previously reported [CITATION_1] .",
